  "id": "019d2f1c-e85d-7e22-8d7c-5e852cf29728",
  "content": "## GC Worker Skeleton Implementation (Issue #19)\n\nImplemented the background GC worker for tiered knowledge lifecycle in corvia.\nThe worker is a `tokio::spawn` periodic task inside `corvia serve` that composes\nexisting modules: scoring.rs, config.rs (forgetting policy), and LiteStore (ArcSwap HNSW).\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Read-modify-write for batch updates**: GC batch writes use `GcEntryUpdate` structs\n   and read current entries from Redb inside the write path to preserve concurrent\n   access tracking updates (access_count, last_accessed). Without this, GC overwrites\n   would clobber access tracking data written between the initial scan and batch commit.\n\n2. **JSON-first write ordering**: Knowledge files (source of truth for rebuilds) are\n   written before Redb commits. If the process crashes mid-batch, `rebuild_from_files()`\n   reconstructs consistent state from JSON.\n\n3. **One-tier-step-per-cycle**: Even with a score of 0.01, a Hot entry only moves to\n   Warm per cycle. Prevents data loss from scoring spikes. Enforced by `clamp_one_step()`.\n\n4. **HNSW mapping cleanup covers Cold→Forgotten**: Defense-in-depth — removes stale\n   HNSW mappings for any entry transitioning to Cold OR Forgotten, not just Warm→Cold.\n\n5. **Config consolidation**: Single RwLock acquisition per cycle (not 3 separate reads)\n   to avoid TOCTOU races with hot-reloaded config. Uses `unwrap_or_else(|p| p.into_inner())`\n   for poisoned lock recovery.\n\n6. **budget_top_n deferred**: The per-scope active entry cap is resolved through the\n   3-level policy hierarchy but NOT enforced by this skeleton. Follow-up issue needed.\n\n### Files Created/Modified\n- `crates/corvia-kernel/src/gc_worker.rs` (NEW) — 980 lines, 27 tests\n- `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lite_store.rs` — GcEntryUpdate, update_entries_batch, remove_hnsw_mappings\n- `crates/corvia-kernel/src/ops.rs` — gc_knowledge_run for on-demand MCP invocation\n- `crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs` — spawn in cmd_serve()\n\nPR: chunzhe10/corvia#36",
